name: Nikon F601 - Mirror reflex camera
description: The Nikon F-601, otherwise known as the Nikon N6006, is a iconic 35mm single-lens reflex film camera that was produced by Nikon in mid 90’s.. It features an improved second-generation autofocus system, motor drive for automatic film advance, a built-in pop-up electronic flash, a top shutter speed of 1/2000 of a second, and a new "Matrix" evaluative multi-zone metering program. Comes with a 35-to-70 mm autofocus Nikkor zoom lens. It is compatible with a wide range of Nikon F-mount lenses, including both autofocus and manual focus types. Great camera for a collector. Is sold with lens & camera bag. Works with 35mm film. Perfect for photography students or photo artists or photography expert.
